IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: The California Nurses Association (CNA) is a 501(c)(5) labor organization with the primary exempt purpose of collective bargaining on behalf of registered nurses (RNs). In addition to collective bargaining for contracts governing the employment terms and working conditions of RNs, CNA activities include organizing new bargaining units, nursing practice education to assist the profession of nursing in maintaining and improving the quality of its service to the public, communication to increase public and professional knowledge and understanding of professional nursing and healthcare delivery issues, administration of the organization, maintenance of its properties and assets and related activities which further the common interests of the membership.
IRS990.MissionDescription: The organization's primary mission is to support and improve the quality of health care and nurse practice through collective bargaining and advocacy for its members on matters of importance to the quality of the Nursing Profession.
IRS990.Description: Negotiated and/or enforced collective bargaining contracts on behalf of approximately 78,967 members working in more than 200+ facilities as of June 30, 2010.

Activity2.Description: Developed and presented continuing education courses for RNs on professional practice issues of interest.

Activity3.Description: Published a monthly magazine titled "Registered Nurses" containing articles of interest on nursing practice, healthcare issues and the organization's activities.

ActivityOther.Description: Administered an arbitration program to provide members with representation in arbitration proceedings to resolve disputes arising under CNA negotiated collective bargaining agreements.
